frameDefinitions: An Agent wants to achieve a Goal,  or an object.
In this frame, the Patient, an inorganic item, undergoes a chemical process caused by another entity, which renders it less useful, desirable or stable.
An organic item, the Patient, has undergone the natural process of rotting  and decaying with a possible expression of the Degree to which the rotting has occurred.
Under some Condition, usually left implicit, a Duty needs to be fulfilled by a  Responsible_party.

listRoleDefinitions: The volitional actor who intends to achieve a goal.
The action or state of affairs that the Agent wants to achieve.
A <fen>Means</fen> is an object or action that is used or designed to achieve a particular <fen>Goal</fen>.
This role marks expressions that indicate an <fen>Attribute</fen> for which it is the <fen>Agent</fen>'s goal that it have or reach a particular <fen>Value</fen> .
This role marks expressions that indicate which <fen>Value</fen> the <fen>Agent</fen> wants the <fen>Attribute</fen> to reach.
This Frame Element expresses a time period during which an <fen>Agent</fen> had a particular <fen>Goal</fen>.
The <fen>Patient</fen>  is corroded by the <fen>Cause</fen>.
<fen>Cause</fen> identifies an animate or inanimate entity, a force, or event that corrodes the <fen>Patient</fen>. Volitionality is not a necessary characteristic of <fen>Cause</fen>.
The individual that corrodes the <fen>Patient</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Cause</fen> corrodes the <fen>Patient</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Cause</fen> corrodes the <fen>Patient</fen>.
The <fen>Patient</fen> is the organic matter that has decayed.
The action that the <fen>Responsible_party</fen> is obligated to perform.
The person who must perform the <fen>Duty</fen>.
The time interval during which the <fen>Duty</fen> is mandatory.
A location in which the <fen>Duty</fen>  obtains.
The <fen>Addict</fen> is physiologically or psychologically dependent on a substance or a behavior.
<fen>Addictant</fen> is the substance or behavior to which the <fen>Addict</fen> is dependent.
The <fen>Patient</fen> undergoes a change.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Patient</fen> corrodes.
The <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Patient</fen> corrodes.
